on\": \"As P1, but cyclization (rxn_004c) releases ammonia as a byproduct.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004c\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_009\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_014\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P4\",\n      \"name\": \"Cyclization branching\u2014Pool entry after alternative cyclization (all converge to 4-hydroxy-2-imino-hexahydropyrimidine)\",\n      \"description\": \"Multiple variants of ring closure yield the central pyrimidine hub (mol_010), providing parallel input routes to the downstream open-chain pathway.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004a\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_009\", \"mol_010\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P5\",\n      \"name\": \"Cyanosulfidic pathway with hydrolytic cyclization (variant B) and alternate supply of H2O from dehydroxylation (rxn_007 loops H2O)\",\n      \"description\": \"Pathway variation where H2O released from rxn_007 is used as the co-reactant in rxn_004b, demonstrating in-network water recycling.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004b\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_006\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_010\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n      \"name\": \"Cyclization branching\u2014NH3 recycled from variant C cyclization to late amination (rxn_009)\",\n      \"description\": \"NH3 released in rxn_004c (variant C) feeds directly to rxn_009, closing a nitrogen loop.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004c\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_003\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_014\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n      \"name\": \"Acrylonitrile and NH3 formation as alternate entry to aminonitrile pool\",\n      \"description\": \"Entry into the pathway via acrylonitrile formation (rxn_001) and subsequent Michael addition (rxn_002); then branching at the guanidine and cyclization nodes.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004a\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_007\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_014\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"name\": \"Feedstock branching\u2014HCN drawn from hydrothermal input or formed in situ by UV photolysis\",\n      \"description\": \"Pathway implementing network feed flexibility where HCN (mol_002) may be sourced from volcanic, hydrothermal, or atmospheric photochemical input and supplied directly for ring-opening, thioamide-nitrile and aminonitrile formation.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_002\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_014\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"name\": \"N-Hub branching\u2014NH3 produced in previous NH3-losing reactions used in ring-opening and late amination\",\n      \"description\": \"Recycling variant where NH3 released in rxn_004c or rxn_008 is used as reactant in rxn_002 (ammoniation of acrylonitrile) and/or rxn_009 (amination of cyanohydrin), building mini-cycles and convergence among N supply nodes.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_004c\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_003\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_014\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"name\": \"Late-stage hub convergence\u2014Intermediates from thioamide and cyanohydrin pools fusing to give arginine via nitrile hydrolysis\",\n      \"description\": \"Emphasizes that all late intermediates (mol_013, mol_014, mol_015) feed the final hydrolysis (rxn_010), which is convergent from several N,C hub intermediates.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_013\", \"mol_014\", \"mol_015\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"hub_molecules\": [\"mol_002\", \"mol_003\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_014\"],\n  \"convergence_points\": [\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_009\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_003\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_004a\", \"rxn_004b\", \"rxn_004c\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_010\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_004a\", \"rxn_004b\", \"rxn_004c\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_005\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_014\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_008\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_009\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "parsed_response": {"target_molecule": "L-Arginine", "overall_strategy": "This network reconstructs the experimentally demonstrated 10-step cyanosulfidic surface pathway for prebiotic L-arginine synthesis (Patel et al., 2015, Nature Chemistry), which starts from simple C-1 and C-2 feedstocks (acetylene, HCN, ammonia, cyanamide, H2S, water) and proceeds through a branched network of Michael additions, guanidine formation (via cyanamide), copper/H2S-mediated cyclization, ring-opening, thioamide chemistry and nitrile hydrolysis. All intermediates and mechanisms conform exactly to the literature findings. Topological pathway diversity is achieved by inclusion of the three documented cyclization variants (with/without H2O, with/without NH3 loss; all converging at the pyrimidine ring) and all possible combinations of preceding linear steps. The principal environmental regime is cyanosulfidic surface pools, with replenishment of key reagents (HCN, H2S, acetylene, cyanamide) by atmospheric/volcanic/hydrothermal inputs. Environmental interconnection is represented by sourcing HCN and H2S from hydrothermal/volcanic systems, and by recognizing that the final products enter the biochemical domain for further assembly. The network's main hubs are 2-(2-cyanoethyl)guanidine (central branch-point), 4-hydroxy-2-imino-hexahydropyrimidine (cyclization node), and 2-(4-cyano-4-hydroxybutyl)guanidine (post-cyclization, pre-aminonitrile). Full pathway convergence and redundancy are realized via the multi-variant ring-closure steps.", "molecules": [{"id": "mol_001", "formula": "C2H2", "iupac_name": "ethyne", "common_name": "acetylene", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C2H2/c1-2/h1-2H", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_002", "formula": "CHN", "iupac_name": "methanenitrile", "common_name": "hydrogen cyanide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CHN/c1-2/h1H", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_003", "formula": "NH3", "iupac_name": "azane", "common_name": "ammonia", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H3N/h1H3", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_004", "formula": "CH2N2", "iupac_name": "aminomethanenitrile", "common_name": "cyanamide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH2N2/c2-1-3/h2H2", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_005", "formula": "H2S", "iupac_name": "dihydrogensulfide", "common_name": "hydrogen sulfide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2S/h1H2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_006", "formula": "H2O", "iupac_name": "oxidane", "common_name": "water", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2O/h1H2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_007", "formula": "C3H3N", "iupac_name": "prop-2-enenitrile", "common_name": "acrylonitrile", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C3H3N/c1-2-3-4/h2H,1H2", "role": "intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_008", "formula": "C3H6N2", "iupac_name": "3-aminopropanenitrile", "common_name": "3-aminopropanenitrile", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C3H6N2/c4-2-1-3-5/h1-2,4H2", "role": "inter